  question: Fill in the blank. _____ learning occurs when the algorithm is given
    unlabelled data.
  answers:
  - Reinforcement
  - Unsupervised
  - Supervised
  - Classical
  maxSelections: 1
  correctAnswerIndices: 01000000
  correctMessage: "Unsupervised learning occurs when the algorithm is not given a
    specific \u201Cwrong\u201D or \u201Cright\u201D outcome. Instead, the algorithm
    is given unlabelled data. Unsupervised learning is often used when you want to
    classify data, but don\u2019t know how to do so."
  incorrectMessage: "Unsupervised learning occurs when the algorithm is not given
